But in Lean, division by zero is defined to be zero, so `1 / (0 : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) = 0`. Thus, we have `1 / p = 1 / r`. Since `p : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0`, we can deduce that `p = r`.

